FRAMINGHAM, Mass. (AP) _ Ameresco (AMRC) on Monday reported fourth-quarter earnings of $28.2 million.On a per-share basis, the Framingham, Massachusetts-based company said it had net income of 53 cents. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were 50 cents per share.The results beat Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of eight analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 44 cents per share.The energy services company posted revenue of $415.9 million in the period, also topping Street forecasts. Six analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $414.8 million.For the year, the company reported profit of $70.5 million, or $1.35 per share. Revenue was reported as $1.22 billion.Ameresco expects full-year earnings in the range of $1.85 to $1.95 per share, with revenue in the range of $1.83 billion to $1.87 billion.Ameresco shares have declined 21% since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Monday, shares hit $64.25, an increase of 12% in the last 12 months.ADVERTISEMENT_____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on AMRC at https://www.zacks.com/ap/AMRC